# ============================================================================
# globalnode .gitignore
# ============================================================================
# Design principle (see CLAUDE.md §"Data topology"):
#   - GIT       — source code, tracked docs, configs. Works anywhere, any machine.
#   - NAS       — secrets, env, large assets, cross-agent coordination. Not public.
#   - LOCAL     — node_modules, build artifacts, IDE state. Rebuilt per machine.
# ============================================================================

# ─── LOCAL only (rebuilt per machine) ──────────────────────────────────────
node_modules/
.next/
.turbo/
.vercel/
dist/
build/
out/
.cache/
coverage/
*.tsbuildinfo
.DS_Store

# IDE / editor state
.idea/
.vscode/*
!.vscode/extensions.json
!.vscode/settings.shared.json
*.swp
*.swo

# Logs
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
pnpm-debug.log*

# ─── NAS only (canonical home on /Volumes/homes/TKC Group) ─────────────────
# Env / secrets / keys — canonical at:
#   /Volumes/homes/TKC Group/GCN/keys-secrets-variables/.secrets/globalnode/
# See .env.example for the required shape. Never commit the real .env.
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
*.sa-key.json
*firebase-adminsdk*.json
.secrets/

# Large design assets (logos in vector source, photoshoot RAWs, mockup PSDs)
#   canonical at: /Volumes/homes/TKC Group/GCN/projects/globalnode/assets/
# Tracked in repo: rendered / compressed versions in public/ only.
*.psd
*.sketch
*.fig
*.afdesign
*.afpub
*.afphoto

# Analytics / tracking exports — we don't track users, but if marketing pulls
# waitlist CSVs or similar, those land at:
#   /Volumes/homes/TKC Group/GCN/projects/globalnode/research/
# Never commit.
*-export.csv
*-waitlist-*.csv

# Cross-agent coordination (lives on NAS, not in repo):
#   - Fridges:        /Volumes/homes/TKC Group/Global_Agent_Memory/fridge/
#   - Shard:          /Volumes/homes/TKC Group/Global_Agent_Memory/shards/{agent}.md
#   - Protocol docs:  /Volumes/homes/TKC Group/Global_Agent_Memory/00_standards/
#   - Project plan:   /Volumes/homes/TKC Group/GCN/projects/globalnode/
#
# None of those paths resolve inside this repo — just don't mirror them here.

# ─── Hopper archives (local sort work) ─────────────────────────────────────
# If you archive items out of docs/hopper/, they go to .archived/ — track
# the archived file (it's the audit trail per ROUTING_STANDARD §3.4).
# No ignore rule needed; listed here so the convention is discoverable.
.vercel
